1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:02,100
(Previously)
Now we have the Mudan with us.

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,500
First of all, I think you should
take the best care of him.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,200
And keep observing how
he produces the scent.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,799
Gaysorn doesn't smell like
that all the time, you know.

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:17,199
A person's body scent
depends on so many factors.

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:21,400
I have no idea what actually
triggers the Mudan's fragrance.

7
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:27,999
Do you really not know
who Scent used to date?

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
I have no idea.

9
00:00:29,001 --> 00:00:30,700
Let me go. Hey! Let me go.

10
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,000
Gaysorn!

11
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,001
Where is Bussaba?

12
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:11,100
How did you get here?

13
00:01:11,580 --> 00:01:13,100
Where the heck is your wife?

14
00:01:13,703 --> 00:01:16,053
She is gone and you will never find her.

15
00:01:16,796 --> 00:01:19,846
Where is the concentrate extracted
from her scent?

16
00:01:23,117 --> 00:01:24,200
In that bag?

17
00:01:27,550 --> 00:01:28,400
Isn't it?

18
00:01:28,550 --> 00:01:29,879
- Move!
- Where do you think you are going?

19
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:30,906
- Where are you going?
- Let me go.

20
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:32,730
- Pruek! Com back here!
- Where are you going?

21
00:01:33,210 --> 00:01:34,920
- Let me go.
- Give it to me.

22
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:35,951
Give it to me.

23
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,240
Come on! Give it to me!

24
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,640
- Give it to me!
- Let it go!

25
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:17,100
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 4)

26
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,401
Gaysorn!

27
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:27,403
Hey!

28
00:04:44,093 --> 00:04:45,094
Gaysorn!

29
00:04:51,273 --> 00:04:53,003
Are you okay?

30
00:04:55,293 --> 00:04:56,563
I can't.

31
00:04:58,506 --> 00:04:59,507
I can't swim.

32
00:05:00,283 --> 00:05:01,284
It's okay,

33
00:05:06,346 --> 00:05:07,347
you're fine now.

34
00:05:11,226 --> 00:05:12,227
There, there.

35
00:05:14,483 --> 00:05:15,484
It's fine.

36
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,661
You're going to be fine.

37
00:05:44,426 --> 00:05:45,963
Let's go, let's go home.

38
00:06:16,723 --> 00:06:17,724
This prank isn't funny.

39
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:20,134
That wasn't my intention.

40
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:04,443
Have some water.

41
00:07:14,483 --> 00:07:17,404
Please have some water
so you'll feel better.

42
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:20,581
It's okay.

43
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,161
How are you feeling?

44
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:42,181
Any better?

45
00:07:53,876 --> 00:07:55,277
I don't understand,

46
00:07:57,053 --> 00:07:59,054
I've never harmed him.

47
00:08:00,233 --> 00:08:02,723
Why did he do that to me?

48
00:08:03,923 --> 00:08:04,966
It's alright.

49
00:08:06,763 --> 00:08:08,243
Ray is weird as usual.

50
00:08:08,923 --> 00:08:09,924
Don't mind him.

51
00:08:12,486 --> 00:08:14,403
The outside world is scary,

52
00:08:16,606 --> 00:08:18,563
just like what Mata told me.

53
00:08:27,973 --> 00:08:28,974
I'm sorry.

54
00:08:31,046 --> 00:08:32,885
I didn't take a good care of you.

55
00:08:36,483 --> 00:08:37,484
I'm really sorry.

56
00:08:43,403 --> 00:08:45,883
I won't let anything hurt you again,

57
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,401
please trust me.

58
00:08:56,553 --> 00:08:57,554
I trust you.

59
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:08,060
You said that that the fragrance
from Mudan people is just a myth?

60
00:16:11,137 --> 00:16:12,780
I didn't know you back then.

61
00:16:14,710 --> 00:16:17,373
Do all your people smell nice like this?

62
00:16:18,168 --> 00:16:19,169
Yeah.

63
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:22,646
But when I was at your village,

64
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:26,460
I never smelled this
scent on other people...?

65
00:16:29,003 --> 00:16:30,633
I can't tell you, it's a secret.

66
00:16:31,723 --> 00:16:32,724
What?

67
00:16:34,216 --> 00:16:36,626
Sometimes you are fragrant,

68
00:16:37,063 --> 00:16:38,120
and sometimes you aren't.

69
00:16:38,769 --> 00:16:39,770
Why's that?

70
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,821
You're asking too many questions.

71
00:16:42,997 --> 00:16:44,360
Well, I want to know you.

72
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,761
Please tell me.

73
00:16:47,743 --> 00:16:48,744
You're not telling?

74
00:16:52,983 --> 00:16:53,984
You're not telling me?

75
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:55,261
Nope.

76
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:56,680
Are you going to tell me now?

77
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:58,301
Are you?

78
00:16:58,677 --> 00:17:00,600
- Are you?
- Fine!

79
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,160
I'll tell you.

80
00:17:03,497 --> 00:17:04,498
That's enough.

81
00:17:09,523 --> 00:17:10,524
Well…

82
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:12,771
When Mudan people

83
00:17:13,763 --> 00:17:15,920
are fully developed,

84
00:17:17,663 --> 00:17:19,520
, they bloom like flowers

85
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,520
they've grown enough to be pollinated.

86
00:17:25,703 --> 00:17:27,360
When we see our mates,

87
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,720
our hearts will beat fast

88
00:17:34,123 --> 00:17:35,721
and our body will release scents

89
00:17:38,827 --> 00:17:39,827
to attract our mates.

90
00:17:41,797 --> 00:17:42,920
Just like flowers

91
00:17:44,217 --> 00:17:45,218
attracting insects.

92
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:49,671
Wait,

93
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:53,441
but I smelled you
since the first time that we met.

94
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,560
You've liked me since that day?

95
00:18:01,857 --> 00:18:02,858
Why are you laughing?

96
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:05,320
Just happy.

97
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:07,391
Do you know why?

98
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:11,160
It's because I've liked you
since that day too.

99
00:18:25,650 --> 00:18:27,301
I was going to ask you last night,

100
00:18:29,357 --> 00:18:30,358
what is this mark?

101
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:39,200
We all have the flower
birthmark on our bodies.

102
00:18:40,623 --> 00:18:42,023
Some people have it on their backs,

103
00:18:43,057 --> 00:18:44,400
some have it on their arms,

104
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:46,350
the sizes vary.

105
00:18:47,317 --> 00:18:48,318
But this mark

106
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,920
will indicate who is from the Mudan tribe

107
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,401
and who is an outsider.

108
00:19:03,190 --> 00:19:05,120
Can you summarize the news
from yesterday for me?

109
00:19:06,310 --> 00:19:09,160
Give me all views and engagements
from all platforms.

110
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:22,761
And…

111
00:19:23,090 --> 00:19:25,880
if someone asked about a person
falling into the pool last night,

112
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,240
tell them that it was an accident.

113
00:19:39,963 --> 00:19:41,680
You're not going to call and apologize?

114
00:19:42,477 --> 00:19:43,478
Do I have to apologize?

115
00:19:44,351 --> 00:19:45,393
He was so dramatic.

116
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:49,080
But I didn't mean to.

117
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:53,120
Who'd have known that
some people still can't swim?

118
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:56,880
Whether it was your intention or
not, you should apologize to him.

119
00:19:56,983 --> 00:19:58,503
So he won't drag you to the police.

120
00:20:03,210 --> 00:20:04,880
Come on,

121
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,880
if he decided to press charges,

122
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,960
and you needed to talk to the police,

123
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:11,880
your reputation will be tainted.

124
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,401
Come on.

125
00:20:33,643 --> 00:20:36,520
You're hanging out with him every day,
and you still can't find out?

126
00:20:36,797 --> 00:20:38,440
Are you not taking it seriously?

127
00:20:38,757 --> 00:20:40,730
Your dad's condition can't wait any longer.

128
00:21:04,443 --> 00:21:05,563
Please give us some privacy.

129
00:21:05,843 --> 00:21:06,844
Sure.

130
00:21:11,596 --> 00:21:14,013
Scent, I'm with your dad.

131
00:21:14,856 --> 00:21:17,079
Tell him what you just found out.

132
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,080
Hey, dad.

133
00:21:20,383 --> 00:21:21,400
I figured out

134
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:23,699
when Mudan people can release their scent.

135
00:21:24,917 --> 00:21:26,200
It's when they are in love.

136
00:21:26,677 --> 00:21:27,877
Gaysorn fell in love with me.

137
00:21:28,317 --> 00:21:29,560
So he can release his scent.

138
00:21:30,401 --> 00:21:31,840
Well don, Scent.

139
00:21:32,103 --> 00:21:33,480
You did a great job.

140
00:21:58,471 --> 00:21:59,561
Our scent

141
00:21:59,723 --> 00:22:01,761
is contained in oil from our skin.

142
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,760
When we touch fabrics

143
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,401
the oil from our skin
will transfer to the fabrics

144
00:22:06,797 --> 00:22:08,200
and our scents will linger there.

145
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:11,960
The hydro-distillation will extract
the scented oil from our body.

146
00:22:17,063 --> 00:22:18,410
The final result will be

147
00:22:18,617 --> 00:22:19,760
an essential oil.

148
00:22:26,490 --> 00:22:27,850
It's fragrant, but in a weird way.

149
00:22:29,103 --> 00:22:31,960
It smells like flowers
but I can't pinpoint which one.

150
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,281
It reminds me of

151
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,081
warmth,

152
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:38,241
and happiness.

153
00:22:41,217 --> 00:22:42,218
It's too bad that

154
00:22:42,810 --> 00:22:43,811
it is too light.

155
00:22:44,477 --> 00:22:46,437
It's not enough to
make the fragrance concentrate.

156
00:22:47,109 --> 00:22:48,110
Let me see.

157
00:22:54,010 --> 00:22:55,011
You're right.

158
00:22:58,203 --> 00:23:00,520
But Gaysorn's scent was
all over the house last night.

159
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,680
Why does it smell like
this after an extraction?

160
00:23:07,001 --> 00:23:09,520
I think there was fabric softener

161
00:23:09,743 --> 00:23:11,324
lingering on the pillow case.

162
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,920
So their scents mixed up like this.

163
00:23:16,817 --> 00:23:17,818
What should we do?

164
00:23:22,517 --> 00:23:25,120
I need fabrics with stronger scent of his.

165
00:23:26,482 --> 00:23:28,600
I need only his scent on the fabrics.

166
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,480
You need to discard all perfumes

167
00:23:38,677 --> 00:23:40,520
or scented items like

168
00:23:40,583 --> 00:23:42,717
soap, shampoo or fabric softener

169
00:23:42,943 --> 00:23:44,200
out of your house, all of it.

170
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:46,617
You need to switch the items
to fragrance-free types instead.

171
00:23:46,641 --> 00:23:48,801
I need his clothes to contain

172
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:50,920
only his scent.

173
00:23:55,163 --> 00:23:56,164
What are you doing?

174
00:24:04,677 --> 00:24:05,678
I…

175
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,296
Can you go and check who is at the door?

176
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:18,680
I need to throw all of these away.

177
00:24:32,343 --> 00:24:34,120
Hello, is this Mr. Scent's house?

178
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:38,120
Mr. Ray ordered this
bouquet to be sent here.

179
00:24:41,870 --> 00:24:42,871
Thank you.

180
00:24:52,077 --> 00:24:55,040
You really didn't know who Scent's ex is?

181
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,081
Whose bouquet is this?

182
00:25:17,243 --> 00:25:18,244
It's yours.

183
00:25:18,844 --> 00:25:20,200
That Ray guy sent it to you.

184
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:56,600
This isn't mine, it's yours.

185
00:26:01,003 --> 00:26:02,004
I can't read.

186
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,441
He said that

187
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:06,720
he doesn't normally apologize to anyone.

188
00:26:07,663 --> 00:26:09,863
But he was sorry for causing
you to fall into the pool.

189
00:26:10,230 --> 00:26:11,510
He hoped that you would be okay.

190
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:17,281
Just take it.

191
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:21,240
If it's not for him, then
think about the flowers.

192
00:26:22,630 --> 00:26:24,430
Don't you feel bad for
them? They're pretty.

193
00:26:32,590 --> 00:26:34,480
Actually, I'm not mad at him anymore.

194
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:38,561
What about me?

195
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:40,640
Are you still mad at me?

196
00:26:45,697 --> 00:26:46,698
Nope.

197
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:50,191
Nope?

198
00:26:51,063 --> 00:26:53,240
What do you call the way you're acting now?

199
00:26:54,823 --> 00:26:55,824
Jealous?

200
00:26:56,790 --> 00:26:57,791
Are you jealous of me?

201
00:27:03,683 --> 00:27:04,684
I am not.

202
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:18,641
If you're not,

203
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:20,840
why do I smell you?

204
00:27:23,523 --> 00:27:24,524
Or?

205
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:27,790
You wanted to do it with me again.

206
00:27:28,094 --> 00:27:29,095
What?

207
00:27:29,963 --> 00:27:30,964
Hey!

208
00:27:32,100 --> 00:27:35,100
You can't seduce me
with your scent like this all the time.

209
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:41,631
This is no good.

210
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:44,561
I think we both

211
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,360
need to find something else to do.

212
00:27:47,700 --> 00:27:49,960
Before doing something else,

213
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,881
I want to do it with you.

214
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:30,051
Here's some water.

215
00:28:37,763 --> 00:28:38,764
Let me wipe your sweat.

216
00:28:53,717 --> 00:28:54,917
You think it is going to work?

217
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:58,041
Let me give it a try.

218
00:29:27,890 --> 00:29:30,280
This is all we get after distillation.

219
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:35,401
Let me test it.

220
00:29:55,443 --> 00:29:56,444
Smells nice,

221
00:29:59,277 --> 00:30:00,320
but it's too light.

222
00:30:01,730 --> 00:30:02,920
I think it's way too light.

223
00:30:05,577 --> 00:30:07,560
We need essential oil that is more intense

224
00:30:07,678 --> 00:30:09,318
with a larger amount,
a lot more than this.

225
00:30:10,257 --> 00:30:12,520
Scent is contained in the oil.

226
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:14,920
Sweat will act as a
leader to bring its scent.

227
00:30:15,617 --> 00:30:16,618
It means that

228
00:30:17,043 --> 00:30:19,223
we need cloths with Gaysorn's sweat,

229
00:30:20,243 --> 00:30:21,244
as much as we can.

230
00:30:27,603 --> 00:30:29,604
Try harder, okay?

231
00:30:30,557 --> 00:30:31,558
For your dad.

232
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:37,081
Got it.

233
00:30:57,003 --> 00:30:59,203
We can extract such a small amount
of fragrance from one piece of fabric.

234
00:30:59,997 --> 00:31:01,360
Is there another way?

235
00:31:01,986 --> 00:31:05,386
This is how the Mudan release the scent,
to be in love.

236
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:07,390
I can't really think of anything else.

237
00:31:07,831 --> 00:31:09,991
We need to wipe off his sweat
when he is still in love.

238
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,800
What do you expect me to do
when we launch the product?

239
00:31:13,443 --> 00:31:15,680
He needs to run in a wheel like a hamster?

240
00:31:16,123 --> 00:31:17,840
And I need to flirt with him constantly?

241
00:31:18,066 --> 00:31:19,666
Hey, you need to calm down.

242
00:31:20,757 --> 00:31:21,960
I just need

243
00:31:22,217 --> 00:31:24,320
enough essential oil
to make one bottle of perfume.

244
00:31:24,703 --> 00:31:26,023
And I can do some research on it.

245
00:31:26,057 --> 00:31:28,560
To find the chemical in the Mudan scent.

246
00:31:29,463 --> 00:31:30,464
After that,

247
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,390
we can imitate his scent.

248
00:31:33,397 --> 00:31:34,880
If this plan works,

249
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:38,360
we don't need his sweat anymore.

250
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:42,600
It means that he won't be
involved with this anymore?

251
00:31:44,077 --> 00:31:45,317
If our plan succeeds, then yes.

252
00:31:48,237 --> 00:31:49,238
Good.

253
00:31:54,663 --> 00:31:55,743
I need to tell you frankly.

254
00:31:58,170 --> 00:31:59,520
I don't want to fool him anymore.

255
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:14,040
Mata, I told you to leave it to me.

256
00:32:14,090 --> 00:32:16,240
It's fine. I can do it.

257
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:17,641
You should rest.

258
00:32:18,283 --> 00:32:20,100
Sure, I will.

259
00:32:26,497 --> 00:32:27,498
Wow!

260
00:32:28,677 --> 00:32:31,723
There are many bamboo shoots,
bananas and luffas. Where did you get them?

261
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,641
It's not that hard.

262
00:32:33,797 --> 00:32:36,200
I asked the soil and trees,
and they told me where they are.

263
00:32:39,090 --> 00:32:40,450
Why do you need this much produce?

264
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,560
There are only two of us,
we don't need that much.

265
00:32:44,023 --> 00:32:46,600
I want to sell them, I
want to earn a lot of money.

266
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,360
Why do you need that much money?

267
00:32:51,230 --> 00:32:54,070
If Gaysorn didn't show up in a month,
I will go to the city to find him.

268
00:32:54,603 --> 00:32:56,040
You can't be reasoned with.

269
00:33:06,943 --> 00:33:08,840
We decided to work with Kusuma,

270
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:10,440
because

271
00:33:10,703 --> 00:33:13,700
the company is well-known
from extracting scent from Thai flowers.

272
00:33:14,250 --> 00:33:16,160
Why do you focus on Thai flowers?

273
00:33:16,363 --> 00:33:17,960
They are not flowers

274
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:19,700
but they represent yearning,

275
00:33:20,043 --> 00:33:22,160
and good experiences in Thailand.

276
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:24,040
They will be included in the product.

277
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:25,681
Think about it.

278
00:33:26,810 --> 00:33:29,760
There are so many
tourists visiting Thailand,

279
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,280
Wat Arun and The Temple
of the Emerald Buddha.

280
00:33:34,843 --> 00:33:37,520
I'm glad if all of them bought
just one bottle per person.

281
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:39,920
Thank you so much, Mr. Ray.

282
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:46,601
Why are you here by
yourself? Where is your partner?

283
00:33:47,123 --> 00:33:48,124
He said that he was busy.

284
00:33:48,703 --> 00:33:50,863
I'm not sure if he was
really busy or still mad at me.

285
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:52,313
Should you make it up to him?

286
00:33:52,337 --> 00:33:53,338
I don't think so.

287
00:33:53,890 --> 00:33:55,160
I already sent flowers.

288
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:59,017
If I went to his place and apologized
again, don't you think it's too much?

289
00:33:59,540 --> 00:34:01,000
You know why you need to do this.

290
00:34:05,457 --> 00:34:06,458
Stop smiling.

291
00:34:07,410 --> 00:34:08,643
What do you have in mind?

292
00:34:28,322 --> 00:34:31,385
He needs to exercise and to
keep his heart rate in least at zone 3.

293
00:34:31,720 --> 00:34:34,103
Focus on cardio. The
faster his heart beats,

294
00:34:34,243 --> 00:34:35,323
the more sweat he will produce.

295
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,001
Hey,

296
00:34:39,830 --> 00:34:42,631
since we're here, I think we should run.

297
00:34:43,203 --> 00:34:44,204
- Let's go.
- What?

298
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:47,160
Come on, let's go.

299
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,321
Let's go.

300
00:34:55,637 --> 00:34:57,843
I think we should run faster than this.

301
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,361
Keep up with me.

302
00:35:00,350 --> 00:35:01,351
Wait for me.

303
00:35:20,937 --> 00:35:21,938
Hey!

304
00:35:23,550 --> 00:35:24,630
Let me wipe it off for you.

305
00:35:41,623 --> 00:35:42,880
It's okay, I can do it.

306
00:36:42,943 --> 00:36:43,944
Mr. Sun.

307
00:36:47,157 --> 00:36:48,720
Mr. Scent asked me to give it to you.

308
00:36:49,130 --> 00:36:50,290
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

309
00:37:40,610 --> 00:37:42,320
I will search for Mom in Bangkok.

310
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:45,600
I will be gone for one
month and I will be right back.

311
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:47,281
Don't worry about me.

312
00:38:10,003 --> 00:38:11,240
It's been a month already.

313
00:38:12,797 --> 00:38:15,198
If I'm not going back,
Mata will be worried about me.

314
00:38:19,890 --> 00:38:21,520
But I haven't heard about Mom yet.

315
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:23,200
How could I go back?

316
00:38:44,717 --> 00:38:47,720
It's been a month and
Gaysorn hasn't shown up yet.

317
00:38:48,989 --> 00:38:50,269
He didn't send us any news.

318
00:38:52,090 --> 00:38:53,700
Tonight marks one month.

319
00:38:55,703 --> 00:38:56,943
We should wait a little longer.

320
00:38:57,097 --> 00:38:58,698
How long do we have to wait?

321
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:01,680
You're not worried or
you don't care about him?

322
00:39:02,357 --> 00:39:04,800
What if he faced the same
incident as Ms. Bussaba?

323
00:39:07,358 --> 00:39:08,359
Of course, I love him.

324
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:10,160
I love him and I care deeply for him.

325
00:39:12,710 --> 00:39:13,990
I love him like he was my own son

326
00:39:15,903 --> 00:39:17,704
because he is Bussaba's.

327
00:39:19,890 --> 00:39:20,891
We need to wait.

328
00:39:21,330 --> 00:39:23,931
If he doesn't come back in 7 days,

329
00:39:25,010 --> 00:39:26,410
then we will discuss it further.

330
00:39:43,877 --> 00:39:44,923
I changed my mind.

331
00:39:46,030 --> 00:39:48,720
Can you search for Gaysorn's mom
as fast as yous can?

332
00:39:49,983 --> 00:39:51,240
Keep me posted, okay?

333
00:39:54,770 --> 00:39:55,770
Thank you so much.

334
00:40:36,137 --> 00:40:37,390
- Hey.
- Smells so nice.

335
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:40,360
Are you hungry? I'm making breakfast.

336
00:40:43,190 --> 00:40:44,191
Can I help you?

337
00:40:45,450 --> 00:40:46,451
Wait.

338
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:48,761
Don't you worry.

339
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:51,380
The lawyer is working on finding your mom.

340
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:53,000
He sends me updates every day.

341
00:40:53,561 --> 00:40:55,350
But we have little information

342
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:57,320
so there is no progress.

343
00:41:00,743 --> 00:41:03,800
But you need to trust
me, I won't let you down.

344
00:41:04,744 --> 00:41:07,080
We will keep searching for
your mom until we find her.

345
00:41:07,823 --> 00:41:08,824
OK?

346
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:13,600
I need to say 'OK' back, right?

347
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:18,200
That's right, "OK."

348
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:20,441
OK.

349
00:41:24,100 --> 00:41:25,101
Teach me more.

350
00:41:27,750 --> 00:41:28,950
Teach me how to talk properly.

351
00:41:29,550 --> 00:41:30,640
How to cook.

352
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:32,360
How to use the phone.

353
00:41:33,903 --> 00:41:35,704
Teach me how to do it like you do.

354
00:41:37,080 --> 00:41:38,081
Why's that?

355
00:41:39,443 --> 00:41:40,444
Well…

356
00:41:42,897 --> 00:41:44,297
I think I will be here for a while.

357
00:41:45,143 --> 00:41:46,640
I want to help you out.

358
00:41:47,710 --> 00:41:49,390
I don't want to put all the burden on you.

359
00:41:49,803 --> 00:41:50,804
Stay here for a while?

360
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:53,641
Sure.

361
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:57,160
I will teach you. First things first,

362
00:41:58,223 --> 00:41:59,800
how to say hi in the French way.

363
00:42:00,697 --> 00:42:01,737
You need to pay attention.

364
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:09,560
If someone did this to you,

365
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:12,880
you needed to do it back, to be polite.

366
00:42:13,790 --> 00:42:15,691
Come on, let's try.

367
00:42:25,490 --> 00:42:26,491
What?

368
00:42:27,083 --> 00:42:28,084
It burned.

369
00:42:31,395 --> 00:42:32,621
"This time is better but
still not enough, bring more"

370
00:42:38,340 --> 00:42:41,641
"This time is better but
still not enough, bring more"

371
00:42:59,017 --> 00:43:00,018
What's up?

372
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:01,681
You still want more?

373
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:04,320
You just need it to analyze,
why do you keep asking me for it?

374
00:43:04,370 --> 00:43:06,119
This will be the last time I ask you.

375
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:08,070
We're about to get our
first bottle of perfume.

376
00:43:08,330 --> 00:43:09,331
The last time for sure?

377
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:11,650
Sure, what is the matter with you?

378
00:43:12,013 --> 00:43:13,450
You're working in the lab.

379
00:43:13,653 --> 00:43:16,093
But I am the one who needs to
lie to Gaysorn every single day.

380
00:43:16,560 --> 00:43:17,730
We're getting there.

381
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,640
Are you sure that Scent will be here?

382
00:43:43,530 --> 00:43:46,050
I'm sure. I've been watching them.

383
00:43:46,373 --> 00:43:48,093
Scent takes his boyfriend to run every day.

384
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:49,881
This is so not him.

385
00:43:50,970 --> 00:43:52,850
He only played games or watched soccer.

386
00:43:53,570 --> 00:43:56,490
Well, his boyfriend is cute.
He wants to show him off.

387
00:44:00,427 --> 00:44:01,428
Wait,

388
00:44:02,887 --> 00:44:06,050
you dragged me all the way here
because you wanted to see Gaysorn?

389
00:44:07,967 --> 00:44:10,610
Don't be jealous, we're just friends.

390
00:44:12,490 --> 00:44:13,530
I'm not jealous.

391
00:44:14,693 --> 00:44:16,923
I just don't like to be used.

392
00:44:17,427 --> 00:44:19,730
I'm not using you, this
is a win-win situation.

393
00:44:20,113 --> 00:44:22,490
You got your business
deal and I got a new boy.

394
00:44:22,730 --> 00:44:23,731
One more thing,

395
00:44:24,613 --> 00:44:26,253
we can get in a way of Scent's happiness.

396
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:30,130
So it's a win-win, okay?

397
00:44:34,130 --> 00:44:35,650
OK. Deal.

398
00:44:43,427 --> 00:44:45,530
Hey, I don't want to run anymore.

399
00:44:48,610 --> 00:44:50,210
We're here already, just enjoy it.

400
00:44:51,107 --> 00:44:52,350
I don't want to be here either.

401
00:44:53,033 --> 00:44:54,153
I want to go somewhere else.

402
00:44:55,034 --> 00:44:57,810
Why do we have to be here every day?
Why do we have to run every day?

403
00:44:58,793 --> 00:45:00,530
People here don't have anything else to do?

404
00:45:02,673 --> 00:45:03,674
Let's go.

405
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:06,720
We haven't run to that side yet,
let's go have a look.

406
00:45:07,750 --> 00:45:08,751
Let's go.

407
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:27,423
Look! So many fish.

408
00:45:32,387 --> 00:45:34,290
- Hey! My necklace!
- What?

409
00:45:34,413 --> 00:45:35,733
- That's my necklace!
- Follow me.

410
00:45:36,490 --> 00:45:37,491
Stop it! Hey!

411
00:45:38,427 --> 00:45:39,428
Stop!

412
00:45:40,460 --> 00:45:42,970
- Stop running!
- My necklace!

413
00:45:43,343 --> 00:45:45,103
Help! Help!

414
00:45:45,690 --> 00:45:47,350
Catch the thief!

415
00:45:47,770 --> 00:45:48,771
My necklace!

416
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:50,241
Come here, fast.

417
00:45:50,433 --> 00:45:52,234
Help! Help!

418
00:45:52,333 --> 00:45:53,334
My necklace!

419
00:45:54,850 --> 00:45:57,130
Thief! Thief!

420
00:45:57,330 --> 00:45:58,331
My necklace!

421
00:45:59,013 --> 00:46:00,014
The necklace.

422
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:05,681
It's mine.

423
00:46:09,667 --> 00:46:10,668
It's yours.

424
00:46:12,420 --> 00:46:16,330
You're lucky that
Mekin and I happened to be here.

425
00:46:17,060 --> 00:46:18,860
Such a coincidence,
we got your necklace back.

426
00:46:20,693 --> 00:46:21,694
Oh, yeah?

427
00:46:23,770 --> 00:46:25,050
My necklace is worth nothing.

428
00:46:25,850 --> 00:46:27,370
Why did he want it?

429
00:46:28,040 --> 00:46:29,090
If he wanted money,

430
00:46:30,733 --> 00:46:32,170
he should have robbed you instead.

431
00:46:32,533 --> 00:46:33,534
Hey!

432
00:46:34,693 --> 00:46:36,413
We were kind enough to get it back to you.

433
00:46:36,780 --> 00:46:38,153
You're so ungrateful.

434
00:46:38,631 --> 00:46:40,632
You? Risking your life to save others?

435
00:46:41,647 --> 00:46:42,648
I don't think so.

436
00:46:43,183 --> 00:46:45,383
Besides, this isn't the place
where you two would hang out.

437
00:46:46,423 --> 00:46:47,943
If you said that it was a coincidence,

438
00:46:48,810 --> 00:46:50,350
I think it looked like it was planned.

439
00:46:51,030 --> 00:46:52,570
I'm from the mountains,

440
00:46:53,509 --> 00:46:54,890
and I don't know much.

441
00:46:55,913 --> 00:46:58,370
But I can tell if someone is scared or not.

442
00:46:59,463 --> 00:47:00,570
This isn't how that looks like.

443
00:47:01,486 --> 00:47:04,450
You didn't look scared
when you ran to the thief.

444
00:47:06,750 --> 00:47:07,751
Or…

445
00:47:09,220 --> 00:47:10,690
he wasn't really a thief?

446
00:47:14,050 --> 00:47:16,100
I told you I don't want to fucking do it.

447
00:47:18,880 --> 00:47:19,881
Well…

448
00:47:21,173 --> 00:47:22,174
I…

449
00:47:22,787 --> 00:47:24,370
You refused to talk to Ray.

450
00:47:24,673 --> 00:47:27,730
He wanted to apologize for
pushing you into the pool.

451
00:47:28,490 --> 00:47:30,730
He sent you flowers and you ignored him.

452
00:47:31,133 --> 00:47:34,090
So we had to do it this way.

453
00:47:34,970 --> 00:47:35,971
This way?

454
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:38,480
This is all you can come up with?

455
00:47:43,703 --> 00:47:45,663
Forget about it, we're talking finally.

456
00:47:46,453 --> 00:47:48,454
Apologize to him, come on.

457
00:47:49,963 --> 00:47:51,050
Go on.

458
00:47:52,733 --> 00:47:53,734
Hurry up.

459
00:47:55,187 --> 00:47:56,188
I'm sorry.

460
00:48:01,093 --> 00:48:02,094
What do you think?

461
00:48:08,093 --> 00:48:09,410
I'm not mad anymore.

462
00:48:13,013 --> 00:48:14,014
It's settled then.

463
00:48:14,692 --> 00:48:16,609
Excuse us.

464
00:48:16,890 --> 00:48:17,891
We have something to do.

465
00:48:30,187 --> 00:48:31,290
Have some water.

466
00:48:37,599 --> 00:48:39,800
This will be the last time I ask you.

467
00:48:40,300 --> 00:48:42,180
We're about to get our
first bottle of perfume.

468
00:48:49,227 --> 00:48:50,228
You're so sweaty.

469
00:48:52,513 --> 00:48:54,150
It's okay, it's gonna dry.

470
00:48:57,140 --> 00:48:58,450
Come on, let me help you.

471
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:08,881
It's okay, really.

472
00:49:09,440 --> 00:49:10,450
Don't mind them.

473
00:49:18,180 --> 00:49:19,370
This is so annoying.

474
00:49:32,013 --> 00:49:33,553
I'm at the meeting point.

475
00:49:49,700 --> 00:49:50,701
Hey,

476
00:49:51,320 --> 00:49:52,320
I'm dry.

477
00:49:55,920 --> 00:49:58,090
Let's call it a day.

478
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:13,450
I need to do something first, you go ahead.

479
00:51:24,787 --> 00:51:26,730
What? You two still here?

480
00:51:35,427 --> 00:51:36,428
This?

481
00:51:36,893 --> 00:51:37,894
Give it to me.

482
00:51:39,050 --> 00:51:41,550
This is the handkerchief he used to
wipe your sweat, remember?

483
00:51:44,207 --> 00:51:45,610
Why is it in the bag?

484
00:51:47,273 --> 00:51:48,274
Let's go.

485
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:49,490
Wait.

486
00:51:50,763 --> 00:51:51,883
I'm just as curious as he is.

487
00:51:52,640 --> 00:51:55,130
Why did you ask a courier from Kusuma

488
00:51:55,570 --> 00:51:57,571
to come and collect Gaysorn's handkerchief?

489
00:52:00,650 --> 00:52:02,730
What are you trying to do?

490
00:52:34,233 --> 00:52:35,953
Do I have to wear this?

491
00:52:40,690 --> 00:52:43,691
You need to wear this
for the place we're about to go.

492
00:52:51,120 --> 00:52:52,490
That's yours?

493
00:52:54,770 --> 00:52:56,090
It's a company gift.

494
00:52:56,953 --> 00:52:57,954
Look!

495
00:53:00,893 --> 00:53:01,894
Isn't it pretty?

496
00:53:02,290 --> 00:53:03,291
Yeah, pretty.

497
00:53:05,253 --> 00:53:06,793
But it doesn't suit you much.

498
00:53:08,627 --> 00:53:09,628
What do you mean?

499
00:53:10,730 --> 00:53:11,731
It looks too cute.

500
00:53:12,027 --> 00:53:14,350
Wait, I am not cute?

501
00:53:19,387 --> 00:53:20,388
- Huh?
- Nevermind.

502
00:53:21,130 --> 00:53:22,770
- Come on.
- I din't say anything.

503
00:53:22,795 --> 00:53:24,915
You think I'm not cute?

504
00:53:29,340 --> 00:53:30,380
What are you trying to do?

505
00:53:31,627 --> 00:53:35,067
What am I trying to do?

506
00:53:35,640 --> 00:53:37,330
No! Are you fighting back?

507
00:53:37,633 --> 00:53:39,734
You're fighting back? I'm giving up.

508
00:53:39,759 --> 00:53:40,872
I give up.

509
00:53:41,313 --> 00:53:43,710
You're fighting back? Huh?

510
00:53:45,180 --> 00:53:46,853
Don't! Stop!

511
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:49,061
Ouch! Ouch!

512
00:54:13,800 --> 00:54:15,999
(Next Episode)
Please, listen to me first.

513
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:18,700
You said once you find your mother,
you'll go back home.

514
00:54:18,800 --> 00:54:20,100
Then how am I supposed to live?

515
00:54:27,700 --> 00:54:30,200
About Scent's father...
if you'd just let us...

516
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:33,200
Your scent and your body belong to you.

517
00:54:33,300 --> 00:54:35,060
I don't want to make
you feel uncomfortable.

518
00:54:35,100 --> 00:54:37,700
I've decided not to produce
the Mudan perfume anymore.

519
00:54:38,100 --> 00:54:39,100
Dammit!

520
00:54:39,300 --> 00:54:41,100
Even if you have no one else left...

521
00:54:41,200 --> 00:54:44,100
I will always be by your side.

522
00:54:46,500 --> 00:54:47,800
Are you Gaysorn?

523
00:54:47,900 --> 00:54:49,700
I have something to discuss with you.
